#Descriptive Analysis

Descriptive Analysis provides an initial overview of the dataset by summarizing its structure, data types, and statistical properties. It helps in understanding the dataset before performing preprocessing, visualization, or machine learning tasks.

Common Functions Used

- "head()" – Displays the first few records of the dataset, allowing a quick understanding of its structure and contents.
- "info()" – Provides information about column names, data types, non-null values, and missing data.
- "describe()" – Generates descriptive statistics for numerical features, including mean, standard deviation, minimum, maximum, and percentile values.

Importance of Descriptive Analysis

- Provides a quick overview of the dataset.
- Identifies data types (numerical and categorical).
- Detects missing values and inconsistencies.
- Summarizes key statistical characteristics of numerical features.
- Supports effective preprocessing and feature engineering.

Workflow Impact

Descriptive Analysis helps verify the quality and structure of the dataset before preprocessing and model development. By identifying missing values, data types, and statistical patterns early, it ensures that the data is well-prepared for visualization, feature engineering, and machine learning model training.
